<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-147-198 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 779 138</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  May 27 1991 v8 n21 p8(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Cahners-Ziff Publishing Associates LP 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Bell Atlantic to service DEC equipment at NCR sites.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Briggs, George.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Bell Atlantic Business Systems Services Inc. (Contracts)NCR Corp. (Contracts)Amdahl Corp. (Contracts).andO;Ticker:    AMH; NCR.andO;Topic:     Customer RelationsSupport ServicesCooperative AgreementMultivendor Contracts.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>FRAZER, Pa.andP;  -- Bell Atlantic Business Systems Services, a major independentDEC and IBM equipment service, has signed two agreements to providemultivendor computer services.andM;The company has signed pacts with NCR and Amdahl to provide service fornon-NCR and Amdahl equipment in the United States, Bell Atlantic officialssaid.andM;Under the NCR agreement, Bell Atlantic Business Systems Services, asubsidiary of Philadelphia-based Bell Atlantic Corp., will support DEC andIBM computer systems at NCR customer sites.andP;  NCR will service equipment atits sites that is not covered by the agreement.andM;Through its pact with NCR, Bell Atlantic Business Systems Services will havean opportunity to expand in the financial and retail systems supportmarketplace, Bell Atlantic officials said.andP;  NCR has a strong presence in thisarea.andM;&quot;In the world of open cooperative computing, computer services are playing anincreasingly vital role in helping our customers manage their multivendorenvironments,&quot; said Gary Burnett, vice president of NCR's customer servicedivision.andM;&quot;Our partnership with Amdahl underscores the expanding need for competitiveservice solutions in the large-scale systems market,&quot; said Janet Wallace,vice president of marketing development and support for Bell AtlanticBusiness Systems Services.andM;The Bell Atlantic subsidiary supports more than 500 computer brands and morethan 5,000 different makes and models of computer hardware, company officialssaid.andO;</TEXT></DOC>